Robot arms inspect and repair high-speed railway cars at a maintenance station in Shanghai on Monday, marking a significant step from human tests to robot tests. After technological research and development over the past five years, the first batch of robots involved in bullet train testing and repair work has gone operation in Shanghai where there is lot of this maintenance work. They can help cut time by 10 minutes less compared with human work. Photo: ICÂ  
